content.detailedDescription: On april the 21st i decided to catch a ride with my mother to go spend time with some friends. she drove to her job at lowe's and departed from me in the parking lot of the store, i remained in the car with the plan of staying there until it was a little later on in the day when my friends would be awake. i noticed that all around me it grew strangely dark and the sun shone so brilliantly and some feeling or force took hold of me and made me grab my cell phone and jump out of the car and start to take pictures of the event. suddenly two objects appeared out of the sun moving in complete unision with each other and i was in awe unbelieving i was actually witnessing this, i looked all around me and no one else seemed to be aware. one object appears to be an eye and the other is a sort of sphere or u.F.O., these objects moved as if they had life. the sun clearly has a sword piercing through it. the eye went all around moving incredibly fast and the other object followed in the same manner as the eye seemed to be looking upon the earth. also above the eye appeared what looked like a face of fire looking down from the heavens. the objects then went back into the direction of the sun and dissapeared back into the heavens. i still cannot believe it but it happened to me, i would be much obliged if anyone can shed light on the images i have taken because from that day i have been perplexed as to what the event meant for my sake and for the sake of the human race.
content.summary: Sun becomes extremely bright yet everything around grows dark, objects appear from sun.

content.detailedDescription: It was after august 1976, but i am not sure of exact year or month.  we were returning from dinner - the sun was down but it was summer and it was still light out.  we pulled up on york drive and noticed a whole bunch of people standing in the street all looking in the same direction (to the west) - upwards of 30 or so people i'd say.  we walked down and asked what was going on.  they pointed up to the sky.  there was a large, stationary disc-shaped object just hovering there in the sky, with white lights around the edges and four larger lights on the bottom.  it's hard to describe exactly but i remember being aghast, like you can't believe what you're seeing.  my mother ran inside to call the most trusted weatherman and newsperson in the dfw area, harold taft at channel 5, to report it and see if anyone there knew about it.  i was running back and forth between her and outside.  her fingers were shaking as she dialed.  they didn't know of anything in the sky that could cause that and said they'd gotten several other calls about it.  i remember them scrambing to find a camera, but back then they weren't kept on the ready like they are now.  military fighter jets arrived and chased it.  the object would move to a different point in the sky with incredible speed, then again just hover there while the jets had to make a traditional turn to try and pursue the object.  it moved so much faster than the jets that it was almost comical.  it was almost like it was toying with the jets, playing with them or teasing them or something as it darted here and there, making the jets try to follow.  finally it appeared to tire of the game and took off to the northwest and disappeared from sight within seconds due to the sheer speed it was travelling at.  there was a short article in the star telegram the following day, and about six months to a year later there was a follow up article saying they had done research and still had not been able to determine what the object actually was.  i've always wanted to do the research at the star telegram archives or have the other neighborhood residents interviewed just to see if any of them had movies or film.  my father also saw it and is still alive, and i'm sure there are other people still in the neighborhood who could testify what they saw.  i just thought i should document this in case anyone else could benefit from the info somehow, especially since it was documented in the newspapers.  feel free to contact me with any questions - thank you.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Entire neighborhood saw ufo chased by jets from carswell in 1970s

content.detailedDescription: At approx. 1825 hrs i received a call from a friend advising me to look at a bright airborne object in the northwestern sky.  i went outside and entered the street to the immediate left of my home and faced north.  i observed what i thought at first was a planet since it didn't twinkle like a star would.  with my friend still on the line i told him what i thought it was and we ended the call.  i proceeded to get my binoculars (celestron upclose 10x50).  i was able to locate the object and found i couldn't focus it in easily.  with the sun going down i quickly located something in the distance i could test my focus on and found that everything came through clearly. i again located the object and found that it didn't resolve in focus like a star or planet and that it was gradually getting dimmer.  it color was going from white like a star to dimmer orange and that's when it occured to me that it was reflecting sunlight rather than emitting its own light.  at no time during my obervation did it move.  i called my friend back and advised him of what i was seeing.  i also retrieved my digital camera (kodak easyshare c613) and snapped off one shot.  it soon became too dim to observe even through binoculars.  i called it quits at approx. 1855 hrs.  i felt odd viewing it once i realized it was reflecting sunlight and remaining stationary.  i've viewed stars and planets as well as aircraft through my binoculars and this felt different.  i just don't know what it was.  the total time of my observation was approx. 30 mins.
content.summary: Stationary airborne object reflecting light of setting sun

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving to work this morning heading south on i-75, when i looked out the window and noticed a very bright, white light moving slowly in the sky.  for perspective, i was looking diagonally in line with the home depot you can see off i-75 near the tylersville rd. exit.  i waited for the it to start blinking like airplane lights do, but it never did.  the light source definitely was emanating from the object and not the ground.  i watched it for about 20 seconds, then briefly turned my attention to the traffic, when i looked for it again it was gone.  i scanned the sky saw a speck of it miles away now on the other side of the highway.  then gone.

reading earlier reports on the mufon site, this was identical to a report from last night, 9/10/09 with the photos.
content.summary: Bright, white light hovering in west chester, oh.

content.detailedDescription:
I had just awaken from a nap @ approx 1845 on oct.15 2007,monterey, ca. & went outside to get fresh air. i was sitting in a lawn chair, facing south, the sun was just setting, it was a warm balmy, very clear sky, no clouds, no discernable winds...I then noticed a (only can describe as,pulsating orange-ish (golden) light, descending from the sky) and heading in my direction, about 5 miles away, moving rather slowly. as it got closer, i got out of my chair & moved toward the sidewalk to get a better view, trying to figure out what was that pulsating light(not flashing,not stobing) as it got closer i could see that the light was on the very front of the craft, in fact it was the whole front that was the light. i then saw my room-mates wife near the front door and yelled "lisa, lisa come out here!!!" she then came out & we both watched as the craft was passing by and over the roof-line of the apartment,approx 600 feet/altitude is my best guess. we could see that this cigar/blimp shaped object had no wings of any kind, no tail, no cockpit, no undercarriage, no propellers, no nothing, & it was not making a sound @ all, it was approx. the size/length of regular blimp, but was not a blimp, as it was passing overhead, we ran into & back of the apt. to the balcony and watched as it (slowly...65mph?) headed north...@ the rear of the craft we could see two small round (apertures..Both had a pale blue glow)...We were amazed and because, it was from south to north like many commercial aircraft frequently travel, daily, & monterey's airport is south east of my lacation by about 5mi's, could only say it's probably a craft that we have never seen.....But we decided not report to the police, unless we heard ot read if others had seen it, and..It was not in the local papers or tv news that week....Having seen an episode of ufo magazine on tv...I thought i would search for this mufon site(it was mentioned on the show)
and here i am reporting now two + yrs later...I am not sure of exact month, it could be sept. or even november...It was during one our "indian summer" warm spells...I keep looking, have not seen it since.
content.summary: Object seemed to descend from the southern sky, moving northward and continual descent to approx 600-800 feet/altitude.

content.detailedDescription:
This event happened in raritan nj. my brother and i journeyed from ne pa. to raritan nj in order to attend the wake and funeral of our aunt who just passed away. the wake was held at a funeral home in raritan.

 about 9:00pm it was getting pretty warm in the funeral home so i decided to go and stand on the steps outside to get some air. the first thing i noticed was that the sky was very overcast and the clouds were rather low, not a star to be seen. by the way, i am a member of mufon and i have had a previous sighting over 15 years ago.

 as i turned to my left i noticed what seemed to be one lone star in the sky. the first thing that entered my mind was how totally devoid the sky was of stars except for just this one. it was orangish and about the size of a bb (as in bb gun). i turned my head back to the front just enjoying the cool air. about a minute later i turned toward the star again but this time i noticed it was moving toward me. i followed its movements from my left until it was right over my head but somewhat in front of me. suddenly the orangish "star" just blinked out and no sooner did 2 lites ,one bright white and the other a ruby red appear, each just a short distance from each other. each of these lights were half the size of the "bb". they continued in the direction of the original light for a few seconds then they also blinked out, not to be seen no matter how i strained my eyes to glimpse them. through out the entire sighting the lights emitted nothing but total silence as far as sound was concerned.

 i was told that this area is a busy corrider for commercial aircraft. later that nite we all gathered on my cousin's patio and i observed a number of aircraft fly over which were immediately recognizable as such going by lite pattern and engine sound. what i observed earlier was totally different as far as sound (lack of) and lite pattern , not to mention behavior.
content.summary: Size and shape of normal star. blinked out and 2 smaller lights appeared half the size of original star sized light.

content.detailedDescription: Skywatching in richmond, ri, my girlfriend and i were waiting for a possible flyby of the space station and discovery shuttle because i saw an official nasa website that listed the flybys in our zip code. the station was supposed to, i believe, fly by at 8:28-8:30pm. we were looking at the stars when then we saw what looked like a very close, bright, whitish yellow star fly into view. its flight path was following the curvature of the earth. i looked away and my girlfriend saw the object turn different colors and grow larger. the colors included vivid orange and green. she then witnessed it explode. i saw a flash and heard her scream. i looked up and noticed just the star like object, but now it had a translucent bubble, oval in shape, surrounding the object. the bubble expanded. it was hard to see. the object then followed on its course across the curvature of the horizon. a second star like object at the same slow speed then followed the first objects path exactly to the same location, this one did not change colors or explode. i have seen satellite and shuttle flybys but these looked too large and traveled too slowly. my girlfriend was genuinely terrified by what she saw and i had to calm her down, which took a while. i was also very surprised to see that and i do not know what to think about it! hopefully someone can contact me with some sort of alternate explanation. thank you for reading and happy star gazing to the mufon network. a.Robert00@live.Com
content.summary: Looked like a bright star, white-yellow.

content.detailedDescription:
This craft was observed while standing outside a home in carter lake, ia on 9-10-9 at approx 8:40pm.  fortunately, i had a new witness with me, though he wishes to remain anonymous and will go by ���jim���.  we had just finished discussing my 8-30-9 sighting and i pointed out the ne area of the sky by the constellation cassiopeia where we had seen that previous object.  at about that moment, we both saw an eastbound craft at jet cruising altitude, just under the second v in cassiopeia.  i remarked to jim that it really didn���t look like jet plane lights, when a series of brilliant, silver-white flashes were seen on the craft.  they were easily as bright as jupiter, which was hanging in the sw sky, but smaller.  more like the size of sirius, but not quite as bright.  the craft continued on the same easterly path for a few seconds showing only some fine red lights, then instantly disappeared from our view.  although there were scattered clouds in the area, there were no clouds to block the lights, nor did they fade in/out.  this craft simply vanished or went under cloak!  jim was absolutely astonished at this point and couldn���t comprehend how a plane could simply vanish.  he works with an aircraft parts supply company near eppley airfield and has seen many planes in his life.  he also witnessed with me the awesome fly-over of the iss and discovery on 9-9-9 that has helped generate so many ���ufo sightings��� over last few days.  we both agreed this was nothing like those human engineered and piloted craft.  i would strongly urge that a foia request be made for the radar data from eppley!  although it���s likely that if they can cloak, then they probably won���t show up on our radar! 

we then proceeded to tell the 5 other people in the house, but my girlfriend who has seen many other objects with me was the only one to come out to try and see it again.  she was unable to perceive anything after 20-30 seconds and went back inside since we were about to start a second game of cards.  then to the amazement of jim and me, the same craft reappeared at about the same height, but now almost directly overhead and moving in a sw direction!  again, we could see some faint red lights, but no clearly defined shape since it was so high up.  the craft proceeded to flash the same brilliant strobe-like lights a few more times, shifted position and vanished again right before our eyes!!!  i should also state there was no noise or contrail from the craft.  in fact, this one seems to resemble closely the ones caught on camera in pa over last couple of months.

this craft is also very similar to what we witnessed on 2-16-9 over offutt afb while driving down hwy 75 in sarpy county.  especially the brilliant flashes of light and the fact that craft also seemed to vanish from view after banking to the north.  clearly, we are having repeated observations in the omaha metro area!  whomever or whatever is operating these craft is perhaps sending signals of some type.  i don���t feel ���blessed��� or ���chosen��� to see these things, but they keep manifesting themselves over and over.  now, i have another unbiased and independent witness to the phenomenon.  that really helps lock in the fact that there is a real, physical intelligence that desires to be known in our conscious minds and daily lives.  i do feel grateful that this is finally going to become a reality for all of humanity!  there will be challenges to be sure, but the benefits gained will far surpass the initial shock to our systems.  i am in agreement with those that believe this will be a peaceful experience leading to a newly formed coexistence with other intelligences from beyond our solar system or even galaxy.  there have been many, many hoaxes and erroneous reports caused by lack of information.  these are different.
content.summary: Observed craft that mimics jet plane, but vanishes then reappears

content.detailedDescription:
I was outside on my back deck on september 9, 2009 after 9pm with my partener looking at the night sky like we do every night. i am a very amateur astronomer and always look up in the night sky, as well as can easily identify the difference between stars, planets, airplanes, helicopters, satellites, etc.
   i was looking towards the south-east and noticed a starlike bright object moving at a strange pace upwards. i watched and tried to identify as a plane but nothing indicated that that is what it was. i followed it for 20 seconds then watched it moved high in the sky and simply disappear. i asked my partner if she saw that and she said no. then 15 seconds later another one went up in the same direction- my partner saw this one and we followed it up. this one got very bright (neither had a trail) then dimmer then brighter again, went straight up then faded and disappeared. it seemed to both of us as if they were moving up out of the atmosphere.
  i kept watching the sky, saw some planes and satellites but nothing like what we had just seen. it really seemed as if something were being launched into space from the same trajectory as the first one. i thought to look on the internet if there were space launches that night but haven't looked into yet. then i realized that launches are never done in quick succession of each other.
  the whole event lasted about 2 minutes and neither of us could say what it was, even though we can always identify objects in the sky.

my partner doesn't look up in the sky as much as i do but we both agreed that what we saw was truly unidentified, therefore we called it a ufo as the most appropriate description.
content.summary: 2 ufo's as if launching into space

content.detailedDescription:
I went outside to turn off my water sprinkler and saw a bright light coming through a maple tree next to my house.  it simply looked like a landing light on an aircraft and as i saw it move through the trees i realized that it was quite low.  when it was directly over my house, out of the leaves of the trees and in clear view, i could see that there were no navigation lights.   as a former helicopter pilot i know what a commercial aircraft looks like in the night sky and there were no navigation lights at all.  just one bright light about 1000-1500 feet off the ground. it's hard to estimate the height at night but it was clearly very low.    it traveled for about half a mile or so towards liberty lake washington, the next town over, and then it appeared to either fly out to space or the light simply slowly turned off and disappeared.  the light was at least was 3-4 times larger than the brightest star in the sky. when i first saw the light, out of trees, i realized that this was not a commercial aircraft and called my wife saw who saw the light as well. i ran to the other side of the house to get a better view of the craft as it traveled towards liberty lake where again i watched it travel a short distance and then disappear.  

i continued to stay outside and watch the night sky and saw a similar pattern of the lights coming into view 4 more times.  they would be bright and fade to dark within a short span of the night sky and again with no sound our navigation lights.   one was quite close to my house and literally became a bright light out of nowhere and then traveled a short distance and faded out again with no navigation lights or sound at all.  

i have seen this pattern before in the night sky around spokane.  but nothing so close that i could truly be identified as a unidentified flying object.   i have seen a craft up close before (30-35 yards away) in 1977 which made me a believer in ufo's.  at that time, i didn't know there was a formal way to make a statement about the incident so it went un-reported.  i am however, a true believer and have done a lot of research and i am an avid listener of coast-to-coast, which is probably the best and most informative (only) real media that addresses ufo's at all. it would be great if our government would "fess-up" and tell us the truth...We can handle the truth.
content.summary: A bright light, that looked like a landing light on aircraft, silently over my home nosedown and then shop space

content.detailedDescription:
I was sitting on an outdoor deck in the back yard of a home, the property of which, borders on sherman lake, in the town of warrensburg,  in the adirondacks.
at about 1:00 am the sky was clear and the stars were out when suddenly i saw what appeared to be two fireballs - one following the other along the same general path.
what struck me was the brightness of the objects and the fact that they were traveling in a horizontal path, parallel to the ground, and did not appear to be at any great altitude. there did not seem to be a tail following them, and if i recall correctly, they may have made a swishing sound as the sped through the air.

abouy twenty minute late, another similar object sped directly over my head, going in the same direction as the others. my son had come outside, and he saw it too. he claims that when it finally disappeared over the tree tops, at that point, he saw another bright light move vertically straight down. i also saw this.

a few minutes later, another bright object zoomed directly overhead. 
following in the path of the last one.

paths of all four sightings were parallel to the ground, and did not appear to be too high up. perhaps a thousand feet at most? i'm only guessing.
content.summary: Saw two fireballs traveling in close proximity to each other, then about fifteen minutes later, saw another and then another.

content.detailedDescription:
I was sitting on the couch and saw something out of the corner of my eye through the front screen door.  it was odd so i got up and said to my husband, "what is that?".  we both went to the front porch and watched for a minute when i told him to get the camera.  it was directly in front of us about 1,000 feet up (husband's estimate).  he snapped a couple of pics and i watched it until it was out of my sight.

it was a very still night, no wind.  there was no sound coming from the object. it moved from north to south at a steady clip, never changing altitude.

it didn't scare us, it was intriguing.
content.summary: No sound, moving in a straight line.

content.detailedDescription: I went outside to have a smoke. i was on the phone with my husband having a serious discussion. the lights caught my eye for a moment, but i thought it was a plane moving thru the night sky,at about 9:15pm. i disreguarded it and continued talking. a few minutes later, i saw it again near the same position, and thought boy it sure must be high up as it appeared to be moving so slowly. i noticed the shape and the red lights, five i think. then it seemed to stop. stay in one position, i continued to talk to my husband, and didn't even mention it to him, but i couldn't stop staring at it waiting for it to continue on it's path. my husband kept saying, " hello!", and we spoke a short while longer, but when i looked up again it was gone! i am not the best judge of time but we were on the phone for about forty minutes. the time between his getting my attention and me looking up again was perhaps three minutes. the lights ; if it were a plane could not have transitted the sky so quickly. a satellite would still have been visible. the lights seemed too close together to have been separate objects, but now i'm not certain. i am at a loss for an explanation. i have seen strange lights in the sky before, but not like this. does anyone have any answers?

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i went outside to watch the space shuttle at 8:21pm. it was a clear night at this time and we could see the stars very clearly. we realized that it was cool outside and went back into the house and i put on pants, a coat and a pair of boots. she went in to grab a coat. we both went out the back door and looked directly up and immediately saw these 4 hazy orangish to amber color objects flying from the south to north direction. we could only observe this/these object/s for about 4 seconds before it/they went out of sight over the tree tops. let's just say "they" for simplicity of writing and describing, seemed to be flying low, faster than i have ever seen anything before and in constant tight formation. and by the way there was no sound of any kind. let's see if i can draw a replica of what i saw off the computer.                
                              n
                              
                              o
                            o o
                              o
 
                              s  

my wife says she saw the same thing i saw, but also thought she saw two cylinder shapes side by side with one little offset from the other.
we went into the house thinking that the space shuttle was flying very fast, then we realized this couldn't have been the space shuttle. we went back outside at about 8:26pm and saw the actual space shuttle, which looked like a bright star flying from the sw to the ne direction. this lasted about minute or so.
content.summary: Four orangish hazy lights, three in a row, one to the side, traveling very fast.

content.detailedDescription:
During a football half-time i looked behind me (west}  and saw a cylinder shape object hovering motionless .  it was about 1.5 miles away at a height of approximated 1500 to 2000 feet. a friend of mine saw the object too.  it appeared to be somewhat illuminated with the bottom portion emitting the most light. it made no noise whatsoever. i watched it for about 5 minutes and then briefly turned around to face the football field (east). when i turned back around a minute later it was gone.  at first i was trying to determine if was a helicopter or a blimp or a baloon. it made no noise and so i ruled out it being a . helicopter.  if it was a balloon or blimp it would move a little bit and it would not disappear so fast.

there is a web site somewhere on the internet that shows typical ufo shapes and a photograph someone took of a similarly shaped ufo. it was the spitting image of what i saw in saint jo  but, unfortunately  i cant find that particular site again.
content.summary: Saw a hovering cylinder- like object during halftime at saint jo high schools homecoming football game

content.detailedDescription:
About 1:30am i was standing on land that bordered sherman lake. this was in the adirondacks in the town of warrensburg.

i was gazing up at the sky when i saw what appeared, at first, to be a star. suddenly however, it began to move in a straight line. it moved
relatively slow, and did not appear to be a plane or a helicopter.

following this, another object began to move. this was in close proximity to the other, and was slightly larger, and appeared as a reddish brown or orange colored light that was not extremely bright, but clearly visible.

i do not recall how i lost sight of the objects.
content.summary: Saw what looked like a star suddenly begin to move in a straight line. this was  followed by a reddish brown or orangy object moving that was not far from the other star-like object.

content.detailedDescription: I was standing in my backyard as usual looking up at the sky, when i saw a very bright star like object slowly moving across the sky. i have seen this object for the past three nights. the first two nights they were in pairs. the 3rd night it was a single light. i did not think it was a plane because there was no sound and had no flashing navigation lights. all three nights that i seen these objects, they were traveling west to the east. as the object floated across the sky, i lost sight of it due to the houses in the distance. i truly felt as though i have witnessed something miraculous.
content.summary: Bright, non-flashing lights moving across the sky

content.detailedDescription: At about 8 oclock my wife and i hopped in the hot tub to relax, we have a great veiw of the stars. at about 8:15 we observed a trianguler craft flying at a high rate of speed heading south, it had three lights underneath, there were no flashing lights or a beacon light.We  did have the noise of the hot tub but herd no sound.The craft quickly left our line of site behind the trees.Just seconds after it left our site an airplane at roughly the same altitude flew over us in the opposite direction of the unknown craft.What surprised us is that even with the hot tub running we could here the jet engines of the airplane as it flew over. we do have a lot of airplanes fly over this area,and what we saw was no airplane.
content.summary: Triangulare craft flying n-to-south  very fast no sound

content.detailedDescription:
On tuesday night september 8, 2009 at around 2215 local time while taking a walk i observed two star-like objects traveling across the sky.These two objects, one following the other, came from the west near the big dipper to my north, traveled in an easterly direction for about two minutes then turned slightly northwest before disappearing as they faded out.

this was my second sighting in a year and my third sighting in my life. i find them to be very interesting and after noticing these latest objects i hope to see them again.
content.summary: Two star-like objects traveling west to east
